"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-25-paris-2024-olympics-super-falcons-begin-medal-quest-against-brazil\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  The Super Falcons of Nigeria will begin their quest for a podium finish at the 2024 Olympic Games when they confront Brazil in their opening Group C fixture on Thursday (today).  The encounter is slated for the Matmut Atlantique Stadium, Bordeaux. It will kick-off at 6pm.  The Super Falcons are back to the Olympics after a 16-year absence.  Tonight's encounter will be the third meeting between Nigeria and Brazil.  Brazil won their first meeting 4-3 at the 1991 FIFA Women's World Cup.  The South Americans also claimed a 3-1 victory the last time both countries met at the Beijing 2008 Olympic Games.  Brazil will be led by the legendary Marta, who has scored 118 goals in 183 appearances for the Samba Girls.  The Super Falcons will also face current world champions Spain and former world champions Japan in the same group.  Randy Waldrum's side lost 1-0 to Canada in their only friendly before the Olympics.  EPL: Man Utd to sign ex-Chelsea defender for Ten Hag  NPFL: Kwara United sign defender, Adekunle Samuel  'I am upset, sad' - Neymar reacts after being dropped by Ancelotti from Brazil's squad  Real reason I did not include Neymar in Brazil squad - Ancelotti  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"